(siren wailing in the distance)

35:50.482 --> 35:52.484
*

36:08.834 --> 36:10.402
Hola.

36:18.109 --> 36:19.378
(crying):
I'm sorry.

36:25.917 --> 36:27.519
Jim.

36:27.553 --> 36:29.355
We haven't met.

36:32.057 --> 36:33.759
Well, that's rude.

36:33.792 --> 36:35.261
You do know who I am, yeah?

36:35.294 --> 36:37.329
I mean, you've been
in my house, in...

36:37.363 --> 36:39.765
in my bed.

36:43.535 --> 36:45.571
Yes, I know.

36:46.938 --> 36:48.206
I came home and
he was just there.

36:48.240 --> 36:49.608
It's okay.

36:51.743 --> 36:53.679
JIM:
So,

36:53.712 --> 36:55.914
how many times did
you sleep with my wife?

36:59.318 --> 37:01.287
Does it matter?

37:04.923 --> 37:07.092
You know, she always
used to talk about you.

37:07.125 --> 37:08.527
"He's such a nice guy.

37:08.560 --> 37:10.696
"Oh, we're just friends.

37:10.729 --> 37:13.131
He's probably homosexual
just like the others."

37:15.501 --> 37:17.503
She hid you good.

37:21.340 --> 37:25.311
You hide too, behind
that little white collar.

37:28.747 --> 37:31.149
(Velcro rips)

37:35.321 --> 37:36.555
So,

37:36.588 --> 37:39.057
who's hiding now?

37:39.090 --> 37:40.492
Leave him alone.

37:40.526 --> 37:42.160
You want to hit me?
I'm just telling you,

37:42.193 --> 37:43.895
I'm right here.

37:43.929 --> 37:45.130
You want me to be the guy

37:45.163 --> 37:46.832
who beats up a priest in church?

37:46.865 --> 37:49.167
I am right here.

37:52.270 --> 37:53.605
No.

37:53.639 --> 37:56.675
No, what I'm gonna do is

37:56.708 --> 38:00.612
I'm going to make a call
to your boss, or bishop,

38:00.646 --> 38:03.449
or whatever the hell he is,
and I'm gonna see how he feels

38:03.482 --> 38:07.185
about the whole priest
committing adultery thing.

38:07.218 --> 38:10.822
My guess, not too happy.

38:16.227 --> 38:19.365
I'm sorry.

38:19.398 --> 38:21.533
I never...

38:21.567 --> 38:23.569
never meant for any...

38:32.878 --> 38:34.780
I'll take care of this.

38:34.813 --> 38:36.948
I promise.

38:36.982 --> 38:40.786
(footsteps receding)

38:40.819 --> 38:42.821
*

38:48.694 --> 38:50.396
Now, local police are
not answering questions

38:50.429 --> 38:53.499
at the moment,
but neighbors say Mr. Harplen

38:53.532 --> 38:54.500
was a bit of a recluse.
(phone dialing)

38:54.533 --> 38:55.501
He lived in the apartment

38:55.534 --> 38:56.868
for a little over a month...

38:56.902 --> 38:59.638
Be damned, Bennett was right.
(phone ringing)

38:59.671 --> 39:02.574
Like he wasn't insufferable
to begin with.

39:02.608 --> 39:04.376
Speaking of,

39:04.410 --> 39:06.378
someone isn't answering
his phone.

39:06.412 --> 39:08.079
...if bombs or
bomb-making materials

39:08.113 --> 39:09.648
were found in the apartment

39:09.681 --> 39:11.583
as of yet, but we do have
reason to believe...

39:11.617 --> 39:13.351
I met him,

39:13.385 --> 39:16.488
John Harplen.

39:16.522 --> 39:18.890
He was living under a tarp,
shoes hanging off his feet.

39:18.924 --> 39:21.359
We also believe that Harplen
was acting alone...

39:21.393 --> 39:23.194
How does a man like that
afford a 20 grand's-worth

39:23.228 --> 39:25.397
of military-grade hardware?

39:25.431 --> 39:27.032
Are you saying he's a patsy?

39:27.065 --> 39:28.266
But again...

39:28.299 --> 39:31.102
I'm saying this isn't over.

39:44.916 --> 39:46.952
You think it'll hurt the resale?

39:46.985 --> 39:49.521
(chuckles)

39:49.555 --> 39:51.256
Can I help you?

39:51.289 --> 39:52.758
No, it's just hard to figure out

39:52.791 --> 39:54.926
what to take and what to leave.

39:54.960 --> 39:57.563
Henry says we could send
a moving company for the rest,

39:57.596 --> 39:59.731
but we're gonna be fugitives,

39:59.765 --> 40:03.569
so that's laughable.

40:03.602 --> 40:05.103
You could always stay
and fight it.

40:05.136 --> 40:06.972
I'm sure you could find
one member of a jury

40:07.005 --> 40:09.975
who believes
in demonic possession.

40:10.008 --> 40:12.478
(chuckles)

40:12.511 --> 40:13.745
Sorry.

40:13.779 --> 40:14.980
Too soon.

40:15.013 --> 40:17.983
It just seems crazy

40:18.016 --> 40:21.720
that I'm walking away
from my whole life, again.

40:21.753 --> 40:23.989
But this time you have
your family with you, honey.

40:24.022 --> 40:25.557
You have me.

40:25.591 --> 40:27.559
Sure.
We could cross-stitch

40:27.593 --> 40:31.830
pillows together that say,
"Mom, a girl's best friend."

40:31.863 --> 40:34.232
Look, I know this is
still new, Rags, but...

40:34.265 --> 40:35.934
Or we could burn our mouths
on this soup

40:35.967 --> 40:38.436
that you and I make
from scratch.

40:38.470 --> 40:40.772
And I know that we have
to build up trust,

40:40.806 --> 40:42.240
but if you ju...
While Casey and-and Kat

40:42.273 --> 40:46.244
prepare to pass along
their rancid MacNeil genes.

40:46.277 --> 40:48.747
(music box plays tune)

40:48.780 --> 40:50.148
Fine.

40:50.181 --> 40:52.518
Forget I said anything.

40:52.551 --> 40:54.653
Aw.

40:54.686 --> 40:58.790
I am gonna forget everything
that you ever said to me.

40:58.824 --> 41:00.792
You little stinkpot.

41:00.826 --> 41:02.828
*

